sentences: Mark Efimovich Zeltser (born 8 April 1947) is a Soviet-born American pianist.
Zeltser was born in Kishinev in 1947.
Since 1977, he has conducted master classes at various festivals and teaching programs throughout the United States, Eastern and Western Europe, Korea, Japan and Australia.
In 1983, a concert by Zeltser in Bologna, Italy, attracted an audience of over 50,000, which has been claimed to be an all-time record for paid public attendance for classical music.
In 1998 Zeltser was appointed Professor of Music at the Centenary College of Louisiana.
His recording with Yo-Yo Ma and Anne-Sophie Mutter of the Beethoven Triple Concerto under Karajan has been included in "The 100 Best Classical Recordings Of The 20th Century".
